{"timestamp": "2026-07-11T01:14:05.792049+00:00", "level": "INFO", "logger": "llm_policy_library.agents.response", "message": "answer generated", "correlation_id": "658725cb-03b8-4af2-961e-bf7ca0294d9b", "query": "What policies relate to logging and monitoring?", "citations": ["au-11", "ra-5.8", "si-7.8"], "answer_chars": 3200}
{"timestamp": "2026-07-11T01:14:05.842801+00:00", "level": "INFO", "logger": "llm_policy_library.orchestrator", "message": "query answered", "correlation_id": "658725cb-03b8-4af2-961e-bf7ca0294d9b", "query": "What policies relate to logging and monitoring?", "answer": "The supplied controls identify several policy/plan areas that relate to logging and monitoring. Briefly:\n\n- Event logging policy: Define what event types the system can log, which organization-defined event types will be logged, logging frequency/situations, rationale for adequacy for after\u2011the\u2011fact investigations, and periodic review/update of those event types [au-2 a\u2013e].\n\n- Audit record generation policy: Provide capability for generating audit records for the identified event types, let authorized personnel/roles select which event types components log, and ensure generated records include required content [au-12 a\u2013c].\n\n- Audit record retention policy: Specify retention period for audit records to support after\u2011the\u2011fact investigations and meet regulatory/organizational retention requirements [au-11].\n\n- Audit review/analysis and reporting policy: Provide audit record reduction and report generation capabilities that support on\u2011demand review, analysis, and reporting and that preserve original content/time ordering; and provide central review/analysis capability across system components [au-7; au-6.4].\n\n- Historic log review policy: Review historic audit logs to determine whether identified vulnerabilities have been previously exploited within a defined time period [ra-5.8].\n\n- Monitoring and detection policy: Define monitoring objectives, techniques/methods to detect attacks, indicators, unauthorized connections, when and how to deploy internal/ad hoc monitoring, analysis of detected events/anomalies, and when to adjust monitoring levels as risk changes; also provide monitoring information to designated personnel/roles [si-4 a\u2013g].\n\n- Auditing capability for significant events: On detection of potential integrity violations, specify actions such as generating audit records and alerting users or personnel/roles [si-7.8].\n\n- Denial\u2011of\u2011service monitoring policy: Specify monitoring tools to detect DoS indicators and which system resources to monitor to assess DoS susceptibility [sc-5.3 a\u2013b].\n\n- Physical access logging/monitoring policy: Monitor physical access to facilities, review physical access logs on a defined frequency or upon defined events, and coordinate with incident response [pe-6 a\u2013c].\n\n- Maintenance logging and review policy: Log organization\u2011defined audit events for nonlocal maintenance/diagnostic sessions and review those audit records to detect anomalous behavior [ma-4.1 a\u2013b].\n\n- Continuous monitoring strategy and reporting policy: Establish organization\u2011wide metrics to monitor, set monitoring/assessment frequencies, perform ongoing monitoring, correlate/analysis of assessment and monitoring information, define response actions, and report security/privacy status to designated personnel at defined frequency [pm-31 a\u2013f].\n\n- Testing/training/monitoring process: Ensure plans for conducting security/privacy testing, training, and monitoring are developed, maintained, executed, and reviewed for consistency with risk strategy and priorities [pm-14 a\u2013b].\n\nIf you want, I can map these policy areas into specific policy statements or a template for each (e.g., required content, responsible roles, review cadence) using only these controls.", "latency_ms": 8089.3, "documents": 14, "citations": ["au-11", "ra-5.8", "si-7.8"], "is_fallback": false}
